# WordPress core block attribute gotchas

Verified against `wp-includes/blocks/*.php` and `wp-includes/blocks.php` in WP 6.9+. **Always check core source before guessing attribute names.**

## `core/post-excerpt`

```html
<!-- ✅ CORRECT -->
<!-- wp:post-excerpt {"excerptLength":20} /-->

<!-- ❌ WRONG — attribute is ignored silently, default 55 kicks in -->
<!-- wp:post-excerpt {"numberOfWords":20} /-->
```

- Manual excerpts (`wp_posts.post_excerpt` field set) are **always rendered in full**; `excerptLength` only trims auto-generated excerpts. To force a long excerpt on a post with a short manual one, either update the post field or filter `get_the_excerpt`.
- To show the full excerpt regardless of length: `"excerptLength":9999` (or filter out the trim entirely).

## `core/query` — taxQuery

```html
<!-- ✅ CORRECT — flat {taxonomy: [term_ids]} -->
<!-- wp:query {"query":{"taxQuery":{"topics":[33742,776197696]}}} -->

<!-- ❌ WRONG — the {include:{},exclude:{}} shape is for custom query-loop variations, NOT the core query block's built-in filter -->
<!-- wp:query {"query":{"taxQuery":{"include":{"topics":[33742]}}}} -->
```

Core iterates `foreach ($block->context['query']['taxQuery'] as $taxonomy => $terms)` — the flat shape is what reaches `WP_Query`.

The taxonomy must be `publicly_queryable` (default when `public => true` in `register_taxonomy`).

## `core/query` — sticky filter

```html
<!-- Featured/sticky posts only -->
<!-- wp:query {"query":{"sticky":"only","perPage":1}} -->

<!-- Exclude sticky posts from a list -->
<!-- wp:query {"query":{"sticky":"exclude"}} -->

<!-- Default: sticky treated normally (no hoisting) -->
```

## `is-layout-constrained` auto-centering

Any `wp:group {"layout":{"type":"constrained"}}` applies `margin-left: auto !important; margin-right: auto !important;` to its block children. Short-width content (short headlines, narrow flex layouts) appears visually centered.

To left-align children inside a constrained group:

```css
.your-group > * {
  margin-left: 0 !important;
  margin-right: 0 !important;
  max-width: none;
}
```

## Core `!important` baselines

These rules from `components/card.css` and WP core use `!important`:

- `.jetpack-card-title.wp-block-post-title { margin: 0 !important }`
- `.jetpack-card-excerpt.wp-block-post-excerpt { margin: 0 !important }`
- `.jetpack-card-excerpt p { -webkit-line-clamp: 2 }`

Overriding them requires `!important` on your margin/clamp rules. **Comment why**:

```css
/* !important overrides the `margin: 0 !important` in components/card.css */
.jetpack-card-title { margin: 0 0 0.625rem !important; }
```
